decks.notes: The deck focuses on utilizing Archfiend of the Dross with Metamorphic Alteration to create a powerful combo, supported by control elements like Thoughtseize and Fatal Push to disrupt opponents. The deck also includes card draw and selection spells like Consider and Dig Through Time to find key pieces, while also having some versatile removal spells like Go for the Throat and Bonecrusher Giant. The lands are carefully chosen to ensure the deck has access to the necessary colors and utility lands like Otawara, Soaring City for additional support.

This deck focuses on using green creatures and ramping up mana with cards like Llanowar Elves and Wolfwillow Haven to quickly play powerful creatures like Old-Growth Troll and Polukranos Reborn. The deck also utilizes cards like Storm the Festival and Cavalier of Thorns to maintain board presence and generate card advantage. Additionally, Karn, the Great Creator serves as a versatile tool to find answers to various threats. The main goal is to overwhelm the opponent with efficient creatures and powerful spells to achieve victory.

The main concept of this deck revolves around utilizing the combo potential of Retraction Helix. The deck aims to use cards like Wrenn and Realmbreaker, Tyvar, Jubilant Brawler, and Rona, Herald of Invasion to generate value and create a potent board presence. Mox Amber and Karn, the Great Creator provide additional utility and resource advantage. The inclusion of cards like Jace, Vryn's Prodigy and Elvish Mystic adds both card draw and ramping potential. The deck also features various lands and mana sources to ensure consistent and efficient mana production.

The main focus of this deck is to utilize the Retraction Helix combo in order to generate infinite mana and card advantage, allowing for explosive plays and overwhelming the opponent. The deck also includes efficient removal and disruption spells to control the game until the combo can be assembled. By utilizing cards like Wishclaw Talisman and Mox Amber alongside key combo pieces like Tyvar, Jubilant Brawler and Ledger Shredder, the deck aims to create a powerful board state and outvalue the opponent.

The main concept of this deck is to control the board and ramp up mana using Omnath, Locus of Creation and other ramp cards. The deck also includes powerful control elements like Elesh Norn, Mother of Machines and Valki, God of Lies to disrupt the opponent's strategy. The inclusion of Jegantha, the Wellspring as a companion adds consistency and additional mana acceleration. The deck also has a variety of lands to ensure a smooth mana base and access to different colors of mana. Overall, the deck aims to control the game and quickly ramp up to overwhelming resources.
